  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Young Biodiversity Artists- Tropical Forest Brazil</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our program gets youth from our local Atlantic Forest community in Brazil to transform knowledge into art. What better way to &quot;leave a healthy planet to our children&quot; is there than to get them involved in earths recovery! 15 students will enter their classroom, the Atlantic Forest, for a 3-week course on biodiversity, history, culture and use this knowledge to transform it into digital art, through photography and editing. All art will be online taking their environmental advocacy international.</narrative>
  </description>
